Police are holding the crew of two matatus plying the Buruburu route for interrogation after carjacking incident on Tuesday night. The matatus were ferrying passengers from the city centre to Umoja and Buruburu when they were attacked by armed gangsters. Police said the first bus was attacked near Burma Market along Jogoo Road. The gang robbed passengers cash, rings and other valuables. The attackers then alighted along Jogoo road and attacked the second matatu. They also robbed passengers before jumping out near Buruburu. The carjacking incident is the latest in two weeks where passengers have been attacked and robbed in city matatus. Click here for the latest political news